<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-02-26T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-02-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/443: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at La Paz</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hazeltine</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">Temporarily at Iquique, to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Iquique</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-26T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            26, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 7.59 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Conditions improved since my January 24, 3 p.m. Exodus continues but
                                much reduced and mob violence has not occurred. I am informed that
                                local authorities suspect purposes my commission. Please
                                instruct.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hazeltine</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>